title: Self-Study: Data Science
content: Utilized Tensorflow/Keras to become proficient in using large datasets and built numerous projects using datasets on Kaggle.
Attended Google I/O Tensorflow Keynote and completing Tensorflow for Deep Learning and Machine Learning Crash Course by Google.
Utilized a range of tools and technologies to maintain code quality, optimize data analysis, and build powerful machine learning models.

title: Self-Study: Backend Web Development
content: Demonstrated strong technical proficiency and collaborative skills by building and maintaining multiple open-source projects.
Contributed to the development of open source Golang framework Go-Fiber and awslabs golang-api-proxy, showcasing problem-solving, debugging, and optimization skills.
Successfully built and deployed cloud compute projects on AWS using modern browser APIs, REST API best practices, and tools such as Serverless/Lambda, Docker, Bash, and AWS EC2.
Utilized a range of tools and technologies to maintain code quality and optimize API usage and build processes.

title: Self-Study: Frontend Web Development
content: Built and maintained open-source projects using React, Typescript, and JavaScript to demonstrate strong technical proficiency and collaborative skills.
Developed and launched web apps connected to complex backend APIs, showcasing expertise in modern web development principles, accessibility, and code quality.
Participated in multiple developer events such as React Summit to stay up-to-date on industry trends and expand my network.
Contributed to GatsbyJS, demonstrating problem-solving, debugging, and optimization skills using tools such as CSS-in-JS, GraphQL, and webpack.
